efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(1)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Utilizes two stacks to simulate a queue.  Push operations are O(1) as they directly add to the input stack. Pop and peek operations are O(1) in the average case due to the use of a second stack to store elements in the order they are dequeued. However, in the worst case (when the output stack is empty), they become O(n) due to the need to transfer all elements from the input stack to the output stack.  Space complexity is O(n) as it stores all elements in the stacks.

